# Epic closure gate (SDLC)

When **marking an epic Done**, **merging the last story of an epic**, or **starting a new epic**, run the **epic-closure-gate** skill (`.cursor/skills/epic-closure-gate/SKILL.md`).

## Cadence

| Event | Required gate |
|-------|----------------|
| Each **epic** completes (all stories on `main`) | **epic-closure-gate** |
| Each **PM_PLAN phase** completes | **epic-closure-gate** + **project-health-audit** |
| Before starting next epic | Prior epic closure **PASS** (docs synced, branches clean) |

Story-level merges still use [handoff-checklist.mdc](handoff-checklist.mdc) only.

## Non-negotiable before "epic done"

1. Merge-ready gate green (`flutter analyze`, Tier 1a + 1b)
2. Delete merged feature branches (`git branch --merged main`)
3. Sync **AGENT_HANDOFF**, **doc/PROJECT_STATUS**, **doc/QC_STATUS**, **EPICS_AND_STORIES**
4. Run **tech-debt-evaluator**; promote to **TECH_DEBT.md** if persistent
5. Handoff note with review + test summary
6. `./scripts/epic_closure_check.sh` PASS (or document waivers)

## Phase boundary (e.g. EPIC-5 → EPIC-6)

Also run **project-health-audit** skill; produce/update audit artifacts and remediation waves in TECH_DEBT before large scope (new solver tiers, FFI changes, major refactors).

## Enforcement

- **Agents:** This rule + epic-closure-gate skill; do not mark epic **Done** in EPICS_AND_STORIES until checklist complete.
- **Humans:** PR template § Epic closure; RELEASE.md § SDLC cadence.
- **Mechanical:** `scripts/epic_closure_check.sh` (local; optional CI later).

See [RELEASE.md](../RELEASE.md) § SDLC cadence.
